# Build artifacts from `npm run engine:build` (scripts/build-wasm.mjs).
#
# We commit the two TS files because the inline loader imports them at
# library-build time — Vercel and other CI environments don't have Rust /
# wasm-pack installed, so we can't regenerate them on the fly. The files
# are deterministic from the Rust source: rebuild locally after touching
# the engine and re-commit.
#
# The raw wasm-pack output (.js, .wasm, .d.ts, package.json) stays
# gitignored — it's only used by the URL-override fallback, which is
# opt-in via provideTableEngineWasmUrl().

*
!.gitignore
!engine_wasm_glue.ts
!engine_wasm_inline.ts
